Podcast via https://d3clarity.com/podcast/user-owned-tech-data-control/


=Description=

"Are you tired of being the product every time you browse the web? What if you could take back control of your data—and even profit from it? In this eye-opening episode of Data Dave Dives Deeper, we sit down with Matt Martensen, founder of User Cooperative, to explore a radical idea: a user-owned web browser that puts power and profits back into the hands of the people. Matt shares his vision for a tech industry where users—not shareholders—own the value they create online. We discuss: - How your clickstream fuels Big Tech's profits (and why you don’t see a dime) - The cooperative model that could reshape digital ownership - The future beyond browsers—could social media, search engines, and AI also be user-owned? If you've ever questioned why tech giants make billions off your data while you get nothing, this episode is a must-listen. Join us as we dive into the future of democratized tech ownership—and how you can be part of it."


